msgid "Privacy kill switch"
msgstr ""

msgid "Configure the glinet-privacy watchdog (iptables). <strong>VPN:</strong> set up WireGuard or OpenVPN in the GL.iNet admin first, then set <strong>WireGuard interface</strong> to the name of the tunnel when it is up (<em>Network → Interfaces</em> or <code>ip link</code>; often <code>wgclient</code> or <code>wg0</code>). Turn off <strong>Require WG interface UP</strong> if you use only OpenVPN or no VPN. <strong>Overview</strong> shows interface status. Stock firmware may offer a separate VPN kill switch — see below."
msgstr ""

msgid "Privacy watchdog (glinet-privacy)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Enable watchdog"
msgstr ""

msgid "If disabled, killswitch rules are flushed."
msgstr ""

msgid "WireGuard interface"
msgstr ""

msgid "Must match the interface name when your stock VPN client has brought WireGuard up (e.g. wgclient, wg0). Preconfigure the VPN in the GL.iNet UI first."
msgstr ""

msgid "Require WG interface UP"
msgstr ""

msgid "Require Tor running"
msgstr ""

msgid "LAN bridge / device"
msgstr ""

msgid "e.g. br-lan; leave empty to use network.lan.device"
msgstr ""

msgid "Physical WAN device"
msgstr ""

msgid "e.g. wwan0 or eth0; required for correct FORWARD match"
msgstr ""

msgid "GL.iNet vendor VPN kill switch (glvpn)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Stock firmware <em>Block Non-VPN Traffic</em> is often <code>glvpn.general.block_non_vpn</code>. Default <strong>Leave</strong> does not touch vendor UCI. Use On/Off only if that file exists. Prefer one strategy: this watchdog <em>or</em> vendor rules — both may overlap. v4.8+ may use VPN Dashboard instead; see docs/devices.md."
msgstr ""

msgid "Leave (do not change glvpn)"
msgstr ""

msgid "On (block_non_vpn=1)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Off (block_non_vpn=0)"
msgstr ""

msgid "Tor transparent NAT uses the firewall plugin. Optional dnsmasq policy sends LAN DNS to Tor. Telemetry uses dnsmasq blocklists and optional vendor toggles. Device profile: apply-device-profile.sh."
msgstr ""

msgid "Detected profile"
msgstr ""

msgid "puli_xe300 = cellular; slate_ax1800 / gl_ax1800 = Ethernet travel routers (no LTE modem)."
msgstr ""

msgid "Board hint"
msgstr ""

msgid "Auto WAN device"
msgstr ""

msgid "When on, apply-device-profile sets privacy.main.wan_dev for Puli (wwan0) or clears mistaken wwan0 on Slate/Flint."
msgstr ""

